  "texts": [
    "ChartQA primarily consists of bar, line, and pie charts sourced from online platforms.",
    "These charts have similar visual styles (e.g., color themes) and lack the coverage of the diverse range of chart types such as area charts and scatterplots.",
    "Moreover, even within their included chart types, there can be significant differences in finegrained chart features compared to practical charts.",
    "To investigate these differences, we utilize Beagle [6] as the control group to compare their distributions of chart features.",
    "Beagle crawls visualizations from the web using keyword searches and is considered to be comparatively diverse among available visualization datasets [75], encompassing charts from various visualization tools and libraries (e.g., D3 [7] and Chartblocks [11])."
  ],
